A '''Catastrophic kill''', '''K-Kill''' or '''complete kill''' refers to damage inflicted on a vehicle by a weapon that renders it both unusable and unrepairable. Typically a catastrophic kill results in the ignition of any fuel the vehicle may be carrying as well as the detention of its ammunition resulting in an [[explosion]]. A catastrophic kill does not preclude the survival of the vehicles crew, for example the crew of an aircraft might [[parachute|bail out]].

